The latest Spider-Man game for PlayStation 4 – released today – is getting excellent reviews. The game, from Marvel and Insomniac Games, focuses on Spider-Man and his adventures in New York – including fighting big crime in the city. “The worlds of Peter Parker and Spider-Man collide in an original, action-packed tale. In this new Spider-Man universe, iconic characters from Peter and Spider-Man’s lives have been reimagined, placing familiar characters in unique roles,” said Sony. Ranking site Metacritic has rounded up all the reviews of the game, and currently ranks it at 87 out of 100. It has achieved six 100 scores from critics, and scores above 90 from big publications like Game Informer, DualShockers, USgamer, and GameSpot. <span data-mce-type="bookmark" style="display: inline-block; width: 0px; overflow: hidden; line-height: 0;" class="mce_SELRES_start">﻿</span>